{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
from scipy.fft import fft, fftfreq
yf = fft(sig)
xf = fftfreq(len(sig))
s = slice(1, len(xf)//2)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
idx = np.argmax(np.abs(yf[s]))
freq = xf[s][idx]
phase = np.angle(yf[s][idx])/2/np.pi/freq
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(14, 5))
fig.suptitle("FFT")
ax = fig.add_subplot()
ax.plot(xf[s], np.abs(yf[s]))
ax.vlines(freq, 0, 1, transform=ax.get_xaxis_transform(), colors='r', label="expected max freq value")
ax.legend();
